This paper deals with the joint design of uplink/downlink transmission direction assignment, user pairing, and power allocation in a full-duplex multi-user OFDMA system. This involves optimization of system performance, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The problem also involves interference management and resource allocation, which are key topics in networking (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses simulation results, which may fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories.
